label.value: Stage IIB Adult Soft Tissue Sarcoma AJCC v7
Stage IIC Adult Soft Tissue Sarcoma

value.value: A microscopy staining method, that does not utilize heat in the slide preparation, used to examine a specimen for the presence of acid-fast microorganisms, specifically nocardia.

label.value: Myelodysplastic Syndrome, Not Otherwise Specified with Multilineage Dysplasia

value.value: A myelodysplastic syndrome characterized by bi-cytopenia or pancytopenia and dysplastic changes in 10% or more of the cells in two or more of the myeloid cell lines. (WHO, 2001)
A malignant neoplasm that is confined to a specific site without evidence of spread to other anatomic sites.

label.value: Observed Area Under the Curve Infinity

value.value: The area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity from dosing time, based on the last observed concentration.

label.value: Observed Area Under the Curve Infinity by Dose

value.value: The observed area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity divided by the dose.

label.value: Observed Area Under the Curve Percent Back Extrapolation

value.value: The percentage of the area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity that was due to back extrapolation to estimate concentration at time zero, based upon observed values.

label.value: Observed Area Under the Curve Percent Extrapolation

value.value: The percentage of the area under the curve (AUC) extrapolated to infinity observed from Tlast to infinity.

label.value: Observed Area Under the First Moment Curve Infinity

value.value: The area under the first moment curve (AUMC) extrapolated to infinity, based on the last observed concentration.
